  "name": "Search/chaining-and-sort",
  "description": "Combined chain + modifier + sort/summary/total conformance tests, complementing Search/chaining.json and Search/sort.json. Ported (in spirit) from ChainingAndSortTests.cs, which exercises a large seeded bundle via _has:PractitionerRole:service:practitioner=<id> combined with name:missing=false, active:not=false, location:missing=false and a second _has:PractitionerRole:service:active=true, then _sort, _summary=count and _total=accurate. The original test's ~40-resource transaction bundle (Bundle-ChainingSortAndSearchValidation) can't be reproduced with static per-fixture PUTs at that scale, so this file rebuilds the same combination of behaviors with a small, deterministic dataset: Practitioner fhir262-cs-prac-target has 5 PractitionerRoles (fhir262-cs-role1..5) linking it to 5 HealthcareServices (fhir262-cs-hs1..5), each service deliberately violating exactly one of the combined filters (hs2 has no name, hs3 is inactive, hs4 has no location, hs5's only role is inactive); a 6th HealthcareService (fhir262-cs-hsdecoy) is linked only to a different Practitioner (fhir262-cs-prac-other) so the initial chain excludes it. Only hs1 passes every filter. Uses client-supplied IDs (PUT) so cross-references (practitioner, service) resolve statically.",
